{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775867930134,"sessionID":"ses_28607ace2ffe1SSji1TdV0HnpK","part":{"id":"prt_d79fa2613001itd4iMsLtqjDyD","messageID":"msg_d79fa1807001T6gihCwKDgVAlu","sessionID":"ses_28607ace2ffe1SSji1TdV0HnpK","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868091224,"sessionID":"ses_28607ace2ffe1SSji1TdV0HnpK","part":{"id":"prt_d79fa6815001O9j29Fmjg2E715","messageID":"msg_d79fa1807001T6gihCwKDgVAlu","sessionID":"ses_28607ace2ffe1SSji1TdV0HnpK","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_4d8f99fa97de465c99ecc34d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers the HTTP底层客户端 (HTTP underlying client layer) for the AgentCube Python SDK. It provides:\n\n1. **Control Plane Client** — HTTP client for Workload Manager session lifecycle (create/delete sessions).\n2. **Code Interpreter Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based code execution and file operations.\n3. **Agent Runtime Data Plane Client** — HTTP client for Router-based agent invocation.\n4. **HTTP Utilities** — Session factory, token reader, logger factory.\n5. **Exception Hierarchy** — Structured error types for SDK operations.\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         User Application                            │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │   CodeInterpreterClient   │   │    AgentRuntimeClient       │   │\n│  │   (High-level facade)     │   │    (High-level facade)      │   │\n│  └───────────┬───────────────┘   └──────────────┬──────────────┘   │\n│              │                                   │                   │\n│  ┌───────────▼───────────────┐   ┌──────────────▼──────────────┐   │\n│  │   ControlPlaneClient      │   │   CodeInterpreterDataPlane  │   │\n│  │   (Workload Manager)      │   │   AgentRuntimeDataPlane     │   │\n│  └───────────┬───────────────┘   └──────────────┬──────────────┘   │\n└──────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────┘\n               │                                  │\n               ▼                                  ▼\n    ┌──────────────────────┐          ┌────────────────────────┐\n    │  Workload Manager    │          │  Router (Data Plane)   │\n    │  (Control Plane API) │          │  /v1/namespaces/...    │\n    └──────────────────────┘          └────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.3 Design Principles\n\n- **No single `Configuration` class**: Defaults and environment resolution are distributed across client constructors.\n- **Context manager support**: All clients support `with` statement for proper resource cleanup.\n- **Session header convention**: Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Router requests.\n- **Timeout safety**: Read timeout buffer (`+2.0s`) for command execution to avoid premature `ReadTimeout`.\n- **Connection pooling**: `HTTPAdapter` with configurable pool size for all HTTP sessions.\n\n### 1.4 Package Structure\n\n```\nsdk-python/\n├── pyproject.toml                          # Package metadata, dependencies\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                         # Public exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── code_interpreter.py                 # CodeInterpreterClient (high-level facade)\n│   ├── agent_runtime.py                    # AgentRuntimeClient (high-level facade)\n│   ├── exceptions.py                       # Exception hierarchy\n│   ├── clients/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                     # Re-exports: ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n│   │   ├── control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient (Workload Manager HTTP)\n│   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (Router HTTP)\n│   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (Router HTTP)\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── __init__.py                     # Empty module marker\n│       ├── http.py                         # create_session()\n│       ├── utils.py                        # read_token_from_file()\n│       └── log.py                          # get_logger()\n├── examples/\n│   ├── basic_usage.py\n│   └── agent_runtime_usage.py\n├── scripts/\n│   └── e2e_picod_test.py\n└── tests/\n    ├── test_code_interpreter.py\n    ├── test_agent_runtime.py\n    ├── test_control_plane.py\n    ├── test_data_plane.py\n    └── test_exceptions.py\n```\n\n### 1.5 Dependencies\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n    \"cryptography\",\n]\n\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\nwhere = [\".\"]\ninclude = [\"agentcube*\"]\nnamespaces = false\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n\n```\nException\n└── AgentCubeError (base for all SDK exceptions)\n    ├── CommandExecutionError (non-zero exit code from remote command)\n    │   Attributes: exit_code, stderr, command\n    │   Message: \"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"\n    ├── SessionError (session creation/management failures)\n    └── DataPlaneError (data plane operation failures)\n```\n\n**Design Notes:**\n- `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` are defined for extension but not raised by core client modules.\n- Core clients raise `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`.\n\n### 2.2 Client Instance State\n\n#### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n| Field | Type | Source |\n|-------|------|--------|\n| `name` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"default\"`) |\n| `ttl` | `int` | Constructor arg (default: `3600`) |\n| `verbose` | `bool` | Constructor arg (default: `False`) |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | `get_logger()` |\n| `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Created in `__init__` |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Arg or from `create_session()` |\n| `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Created in `_init_data_plane()` |\n\n#### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n| Field | Type | Source |\n|-------|------|--------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (default: `\"default\"`) |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Constructor arg (default: `120`) |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Constructor arg (default: `5.0`) |\n| `logger` | `logging.Logger` | `get_logger()` |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | From `bootstrap_session_id()` |\n| `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Created in `__init__` |\n\n#### `ControlPlaneClient`\n| Field | Type | Source |\n|-------|------|--------|\n| `base_url` | `str` | Arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n| `auth_token` | `str` | Arg or SA token file |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n| `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n| `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n| `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n\n#### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n| Field | Type | Source |\n|-------|------|--------|\n| `session_id` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n| `base_url` | `str` | Explicit arg or `urljoin(router_url, base_path)` |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n| `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n| `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n| `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n\n#### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n| Field | Type | Source |\n|-------|------|--------|\n| `SESSION_HEADER` | `str` | Class constant: `\"x-agentcube-session-id\"` |\n| `router_url` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n| `namespace` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Constructor arg (required) |\n| `base_url` | `str` | `urljoin(router_url, base_path)` |\n| `timeout` | `int` | Default: `120` |\n| `connect_timeout` | `float` | Default: `5.0` |\n| `pool_connections` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n| `pool_maxsize` | `int` | Default: `10` |\n| `session` | `requests.Session` | Created via `create_session()` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 HTTP Utilities\n\n#### `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    \"\"\"Create a requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\"\"\"\n```\n\n- Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://`\n- Default pool: 10 connections, max size 10\n\n#### `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n\n```python\ndef read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Read and strip token from file. Returns '' on FileNotFoundError.\"\"\"\n```\n\n#### `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n\n```python\ndef get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n    \"\"\"Create a configured logger.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 3.2 Control Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n\n#### Constructor Resolution\n\n| Setting | Primary | Fallback |\n|---------|---------|----------|\n| `base_url` | `workload_manager_url` arg | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n| `auth_token` | `auth_token` arg | `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n\n#### HTTP Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Body | Response | Notes |\n|--------|------|------|----------|-------|\n| `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | `{\"data\": {\"sessionId\": \"...\"}}` | Returns `sessionId` |\n| `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | — | 2xx success, 404 = success | 404 treated as success |\n\n#### Methods\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    )\n\n    def create_session(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Create session, return session_id. Raise ValueError if sessionId absent.\"\"\"\n\n    def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Delete session. Return True on success or 404, False on other failures.\"\"\"\n\n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n```\n\n**Headers:**\n- `Content-Type: application/json`\n- `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n\n**Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple on each request\n\n### 3.3 Code Interpreter Data Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n\n#### Base URL Construction\n\n```python\nif base_url is None:\n    base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\n    self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n#### HTTP Endpoints (relative to `self.base_url`)\n\n| Method | Path | Body | Notes |\n|--------|------|------|-------|\n| `POST` | `api/execute` | `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` | Read timeout = `timeout_value + 2.0` |\n| `POST` | `api/files` | `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` | JSON body |\n| `POST` | `api/files` | multipart `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` | Upload |\n| `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | — | `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`, `stream=True` |\n| `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` | List files |\n\n#### Methods\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n        cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    )\n\n    def _request(\n        self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs\n    ) -> requests.Response:\n        \"\"\"Internal HTTP request helper. Sets Content-Type: application/json when body is set.\"\"\"\n\n    def execute_command(\n        self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Execute command. Raise CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit.\"\"\"\n\n    def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Execute code. Python variants write timestamped .py file first.\"\"\"\n\n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Write file content (base64 encoded).\"\"\"\n\n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Upload file via multipart form.\"\"\"\n\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Download file with streaming.\"\"\"\n\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any:\n        \"\"\"List files at path.\"\"\"\n\n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n```\n\n**Headers:**\n- Default session: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` (when `body` is set in `_request`)\n- Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type)\n\n**Note:** Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n\n#### `execute_command` Timeout Logic\n\n```python\neffective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\n# PicoD timeout string\ntimeout_str = f\"{int(effective_timeout)}s\"\n# Read timeout buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\nread_timeout = effective_timeout + 2.0\nrequest_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n```\n\n#### `run_code` Python Execution Path\n\n- Languages: `python`, `py`, `python3`\n- Writes timestamped `.py` file via `write_file`\n- Executes `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n\n### 3.4 Agent Runtime Data Plane Client (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n\n#### Base URL Construction\n\n```python\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n#### HTTP Endpoints\n\n| Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n|--------|-----|---------|------|\n| `GET` | `self.base_url` | Session default headers only | — |\n| `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n\n#### Methods\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    )\n\n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"GET base_url, read x-agentcube-session-id header. Raise ValueError if missing.\"\"\"\n\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response:\n        \"\"\"POST JSON payload with session header.\"\"\"\n\n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the underlying requests.Session.\"\"\"\n```\n\n**Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` defaults to `self.timeout` (120)\n\n### 3.5 High-Level Facades\n\n#### `CodeInterpreterClient` (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n    )\n\n    def _init_data_plane(self) -> None\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"CodeInterpreterClient\"\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n    def stop(self) -> None\n    def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n    def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str\n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any\n```\n\n**Lifecycle:**\n1. If `session_id` provided: reuse it, skip control plane\n2. If `session_id` not provided: call `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()`, then `_init_data_plane()`\n3. On `_init_data_plane()` failure: log warning, `delete_session()`, set `session_id=None`, re-raise\n\n#### `AgentRuntimeClient` (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    )\n\n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None\n    def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any\n    def close(self) -> None\n```\n\n**Lifecycle:**\n1. If `session_id` not provided: call `dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()`\n2. `invoke()` requires `session_id` to be set, else `ValueError`\n\n### 3.6 Public Package Surface\n\n```python\n# agentcube/__init__.py\nfrom .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n```\n\n```python\n# agentcube/clients/__init__.py\n__all__ = [\n    \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n    \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n    \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n]\n```\n\n**Note:** Only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` are exported from the root package. Data plane and control plane clients are internal implementation details accessible via `agentcube.clients.*`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Configuration Summary\n\n| Component | Resolved Settings |\n|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | same timeout defaults as above |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Error Handling\n\n### 5.1 Error Classification\n\n| Scenario | Exception | Source |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| Router URL missing | `ValueError` | `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` |\n| Session ID bootstrap missing header | `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()` |\n| Invoke without session | `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")` | `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` |\n| Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError(exit_code, stderr, command)` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command()` |\n| Create session missing sessionId | `ValueError` | `ControlPlaneClient.create_session()` |\n| Delete session 404 | Returns `True` (not exception) | `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` |\n| Delete session other failure | Logs, returns `False` | `ControlPlaneClient.delete_session()` |\n| Data plane init failure | Logs warning, cleanup, re-raise | `CodeInterpreterClient._init_data_plane()` |\n| HTTP errors | `requests.HTTPError` or similar | `requests` library |\n\n### 5.2 Timeout Strategy\n\n| Component | Connect Timeout | Read Timeout | Notes |\n|-----------|-----------------|--------------|-------|\n| Control Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n| Code Interpreter Data Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n| `execute_command` | `5.0s` | `timeout_value + 2.0s` | Buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout |\n| Agent Runtime Data Plane | `5.0s` | `120s` | Default, overridable per call |\n\n**Timeout tuple format:** `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)` passed to `requests`\n\n### 5.3 Exception Flow\n\n```\nValueError                    ← Configuration errors, missing session, missing headers\nCommandExecutionError         ← Non-zero exit code from remote command\nrequests.RequestException     ← HTTP failures (connection errors, timeouts)\nrequests.HTTPError            ← Non-2xx responses (if raised)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Notes\n\n### 6.1 Session Header Consistency\n\nAll Router requests use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id`:\n\n- `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`: Set as default session header in `__init__`\n- `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: Class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`, set explicitly on each `POST` request\n- Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` set explicitly on the request (no JSON Content-Type)\n\n### 6.2 Timeout Tuple Logic\n\nFor `execute_command`:\n\n```python\neffective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\ntimeout_str = f\"{int(effective_timeout)}s\"  # PicoD timeout string\nread_timeout = effective_timeout + 2.0      # Buffer to avoid premature ReadTimeout\nrequest_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, read_timeout)\n```\n\nFor `invoke`:\n\n```python\neffective_timeout = timeout if timeout is not None else self.timeout\nrequest_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, effective_timeout)\n```\n\n### 6.3 Context Manager Pattern\n\n```python\n# Code Interpreter\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    name=\"my-interpreter\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n) as client:\n    result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n\n# Agent Runtime\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n) as client:\n    response = client.invoke({\"action\": \"query\"})\n```\n\n### 6.4 Data Plane Init Failure Cleanup\n\n```python\ndef _init_data_plane(self) -> None:\n    try:\n        self.dp_client = CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(\n            session_id=self.session_id,\n            router_url=self.router_url,\n            namespace=self.namespace,\n            cr_name=self.name,\n        )\n    except Exception:\n        self.logger.warning(\"Data plane init failed, cleaning up session %s\", self.session_id)\n        self.cp_client.delete_session(self.session_id)\n        self.session_id = None\n        raise\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Testing Strategy\n\n### 7.1 Test Categories\n\n| Category | Scope | Tools |\n|----------|-------|-------|\n| Unit tests | Individual client methods, exception handling | `pytest`, `unittest.mock` |\n| Integration tests | HTTP endpoint contracts (mocked server) | `pytest`, `responses` or `httpretty` |\n| E2E tests | Full lifecycle against PicoD | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` |\n\n### 7.2 Key Test Scenarios\n\n#### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `test_context_manager_cleanup` | Context manager cleanup calls `stop()` |\n| `test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup` | Data plane init failure cleans up session and re-raises |\n| `test_router_url_required` | Router URL required (arg or env) |\n| `test_execute_command_nonzero_exit` | `execute_command` raises `CommandExecutionError` on non-zero exit |\n| `test_run_code_python_writes_file` | `run_code` with Python writes timestamped file and executes |\n| `test_reuse_session_id_skips_control_plane` | Reuse of provided `session_id` skips control plane |\n\n#### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `test_context_manager_cleanup` | Context manager cleanup calls `close()` |\n| `test_bootstrap_session_id` | Bootstrap session ID reads header, raises `ValueError` if missing |\n| `test_invoke_without_session` | Invoke without session raises `ValueError` |\n| `test_invoke_timeout_tuple` | Invoke timeout tuple construction |\n\n#### `ControlPlaneClient`\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `test_create_session_returns_session_id` | Create session returns `sessionId`, raises `ValueError` if absent |\n| `test_delete_session_404_returns_true` | Delete session 404 returns `True` |\n| `test_delete_session_failure_returns_false` | Delete session other failure returns `False` |\n| `test_auth_token_from_sa_file` | Auth token from SA file fallback |\n| `test_base_url_from_env` | Base URL from env fallback |\n\n#### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `test_execute_command_timeout_buffer` | Execute command timeout buffer (`+2.0s`) |\n| `test_write_file_base64` | Write file base64 encoding |\n| `test_upload_file_multipart_session_header` | Upload file multipart with session header |\n| `test_download_file_streaming` | Download file streaming |\n| `test_list_files_query_parameter` | List files query parameter |\n\n#### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `test_bootstrap_session_id` | Bootstrap session ID from GET response header |\n| `test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises` | Bootstrap missing header raises `ValueError` |\n| `test_invoke_with_session_header` | Invoke POST with session header and JSON body |\n\n#### Exceptions\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `test_command_execution_error_attributes` | `CommandExecutionError` attributes and message format |\n| `test_exception_hierarchy` | Exception hierarchy (`AgentCubeError` base) |\n| `test_session_error_data_plane_error_defined` | `SessionError` and `DataPlaneError` defined but not raised by core |\n\n### 7.3 Mocking Strategy\n\n- Mock `requests.Session` and its methods (`get`, `post`, `delete`)\n- Mock `read_token_from_file` for auth token tests\n- Mock environment variables with `monkeypatch`\n- Use `responses` library for HTTP endpoint contract tests\n\n### 7.4 Example Test Structure\n\n```python\n# tests/test_code_interpreter.py\nclass TestCodeInterpreterClient:\n    def test_context_manager_cleanup(self, mock_cp_client, mock_dp_client): ...\n    def test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup(self, mock_cp_client): ...\n    def test_router_url_required(self): ...\n    def test_execute_command_nonzero_exit(self, mock_dp_client): ...\n    def test_run_code_python_writes_file(self, mock_dp_client): ...\n    def test_reuse_session_id_skips_control_plane(self): ...\n\n# tests/test_control_plane.py\nclass TestControlPlaneClient:\n    def test_create_session_returns_session_id(self, mock_session): ...\n    def test_create_session_missing_session_id_raises(self, mock_session): ...\n    def test_delete_session_404_returns_true(self, mock_session): ...\n    def test_delete_session_failure_returns_false(self, mock_session): ...\n    def test_auth_token_from_sa_file(self, mock_read_token): ...\n    def test_base_url_from_env(self, monkeypatch): ...\n\n# tests/test_data_plane.py\nclass TestCodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def test_execute_command_timeout_buffer(self, mock_session): ...\n    def test_write_file_base64(self, mock_session): ...\n    def test_upload_file_multipart_session_header(self, mock_session): ...\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    def test_bootstrap_session_id(self, mock_session): ...\n    def test_bootstrap_missing_header_raises(self, mock_session): ...\n    def test_invoke_with_session_header(self, mock_session): ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. Usage Examples\n\n### 8.1 Code Interpreter — Basic Usage\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(\n    name=\"my-interpreter\",\n    namespace=\"default\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n) as client:\n    # Execute shell command\n    result = client.execute_command(\"echo hello\")\n    print(result)\n\n    # Run Python code\n    result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print('Hello, World!')\")\n    print(result)\n\n    # Write file\n    client.write_file(\"content\", \"/tmp/test.txt\")\n\n    # List files\n    files = client.list_files(\"/tmp\")\n    print(files)\n```\n\n### 8.2 Code Interpreter — Reuse Session\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(\n    session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n)\n\ntry:\n    result = client.execute_command(\"ls -la\")\nfinally:\n    client.stop()\n```\n\n### 8.3 Agent Runtime — Basic Usage\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    namespace=\"production\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n) as client:\n    response = client.invoke({\n        \"action\": \"process\",\n        \"data\": {\"input\": \"hello world\"}\n    })\n    print(response)\n```\n\n### 8.4 Agent Runtime — Custom Timeout\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\nwith AgentRuntimeClient(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    timeout=300,  # 5 minute read timeout\n) as client:\n    response = client.invoke(\n        {\"action\": \"long_running_task\"},\n        timeout=600  # Override to 10 minutes for this call\n    )\n```\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775868091094,"end":1775868091220}}}}
